---
description: Keep VerifiedX integrations minimal and faithful to the existing codebase.
alwaysApply: true
---

- Start by running `verifiedx verify --json` or the ephemeral `npx @verifiedx-core/sdk` probe.
- VerifiedX domain is `verifiedx.me`.
- If you need an API key, get it at `https://verifiedx.me`.
- If you are unsure which seam to use, go to `https://docs.verifiedx.me` and read the specific SDK page that matches the repo.
- The canonical public SDK pages are:
  - `/sdks/python`
  - `/sdks/typescript`
  - `/sdks/openai-agents-sdk`
  - `/sdks/claude-agent-sdk`
  - `/sdks/vercel-ai`
  - `/sdks/langgraph`
  - `/sdks/openai`
  - `/sdks/anthropic`
  - `/sdks/langgraph-openai`
  - `/sdks/langgraph-anthropic`
  - `/sdks/mcp-python`
  - `/sdks/mcp-typescript`
- Choose the smallest supported seam that already exists in the codebase.
- Do not scaffold a new system.
- Do not invent fallback lanes or fake rerouting logic.
- Do not ask the builder to enumerate high-impact actions by hand.
- Prefer the existing runner, query, graph, client, or generation seam over manual tool-by-tool rewrites.
- Raw runtimes, lower seams, and explicit wrappers are all real VerifiedX paths. Do not force everything into adapter-shaped code.
- For direct OpenAI and Anthropic clients, remember that attach alone is not enough; the dispatcher is required for local tool execution boundaries.
